.illinois.edu%2F1.2%2Ftoye.html&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-Grusky2011a-3"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Grusky2011a_3-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Grusky2011a_3-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Grusky2011a_3-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation encyclopaedia">Grusky, David B. (2011). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.sociologyencyclopedia.com/public/tocnode?id=g9781405124331_yr2011_chunk_g978140512433125_ss1-273#citation">"Theories of Stratification and Inequality"</a>. In Ritzer, George and J. Michael Ryan. <i>The Concise Encyclopedia of Sociology</i>. Wiley-Blackwell. pp.&#160;622\xe2\x80\x93624<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">23 June</span> 2014</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASocial+stratification&amp;rft.atitle=Theories+of+Stratification+and+Inequality&amp;rft.au=Grusky%2C+David+B.&amp;rft.btitle=The+Concise+Encyclopedia+of+Sociology&amp;rft.date=2011&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.pages=622-624&amp;rft.pub=Wiley-Blackwell.&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.sociologyencyclopedia.com%2Fpublic%2Ftocnode%3Fid%3Dg9781405124331_yr2011_chunk_g978140512433125_ss1-273%23citation&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-Grusky1992-4"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Grusky1992_4-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Grusky1992_4-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Grusky1992_4-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation encyclopaedia">Grusky, David B. &amp; Ann Azumi Takata (1992). "Social Stratification". <i>The Encyclopedia of Sociology</i>. Macmillan Publishing Company. pp.&#160;1955\xe2\x80\x9370.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASocial+stratification&amp;rft.atitle=Social+Stratification&amp;rft.au=Ann+Azumi+Takata&amp;rft.au=Grusky%2C+David+B.&amp;rft.btitle=The+Encyclopedia+of+Sociology&amp;rft.date=1992&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.pages=1955-70&amp;rft.pub=Macmillan+Publishing+Company.&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-5"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-5">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Doob, Christopher. <i>Social Inequality and Social Stratification in US Society</i> (1st ed.), Pearson Education, 2012, <a href="/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number">ISBN</a> <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-205-79241-3" title="Special:BookSources/0-205-79241-3">0-205-79241-3</a></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-6"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-6">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation book"><a href="/wiki/Marvin_Harris" title="Marvin Harris">Harris, Marvin</a> (1967). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=TlgVAAAAIAAJ"><i>The Rise of Anthropological Theory: A History of Theories of Culture</i></a>. Routledge. <a href="/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-7591-0133-7" title="Special:BookSources/0-7591-0133-7">0-7591-0133-7</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASocial+stratification&amp;rft.aufirst=Marvin&amp;rft.aulast=Harris&amp;rft.btitle=The+Rise+of+Anthropological+Theory%3A+A+History+of+Theories+of+Culture&amp;rft.date=1967&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.isbn=0-7591-0133-7&amp;rft.pub=Routledge&amp;rft_id=http